%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20November%202%20last%20year.%20The%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20introduced%20by%20the%20government%20on%20January%202%2C%202018%2C%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20solution%20to%20replace%20cash%20donations%20and%20enhance%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20serve%20as%20a%20financial%20instrument%20allowing%20individuals%20and%20businesses%20to%20contribute%20funds%20to%20political%20parties%20discreetly%2C%20without%20revealing%20their%20identities.%20Under%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20any%20citizen%20of%20India%20or%20entity%20incorporated%20or%20established%20in%20the%20country%20can%20purchase%20electoral%20bonds.%20These%20bonds%20are%20available%20in%20various%20denominations%2C%20ranging%20from%20Rs%201%2C000%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%2C%20and%20can%20be%20obtained%20at%20all%20branches%20of%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI).%20These%20donations%20are%20also%20interest-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20features%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20the%20anonymity%20they%20provide%20to%20donors.%20When%20individuals%20or%20organisations%20purchase%20these%20bonds%2C%20their%20identities%20are%20not%20disclosed%20to%20the%20public%20or%20the%20political%20party%20receiving%20the%20funds.%20However%2C%20the%20government%20and%20the%20bank%20maintain%20a%20record%20of%20the%20purchaser's%20details%20for%20auditing%20purposes%2C%20ensuring%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20funding%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20November%20hearing%2C%20Attorney%20General%20R%20Venkataramani%20argued%20that%20the%20Constitution%20does%20not%20guarantee%20citizens%20an%20absolute%20right%20to%20information%20regarding%20the%20source%20of%20funds%20used%20for%20political%20party%20funding%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20promotes%20transparency%20and%20clean%20money%20in%20elections.%20However%2C%20Mr%20Venkataramani%20maintained%20that%20there%20are%20limitations%20to%20the%20right%20to%20information%2C%20and%20it%20cannot%20be%20an%20unrestricted%20right%20to%20know%20%26quot%3Banything%20and%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20scheme%20in%20question%20extends%20the%20benefit%20of%20confidentiality%20to%20the%20contributor.%20It%20ensures%20and%20promotes%20clean%20money%20being%20contributed.%20It%20ensures%20abiding%20by%20tax%20obligations.%20Thus%2C%20it%20does%20not%20fall%20foul%20of%20any%20existing%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20political%20parties%20registered%20under%20Section%2029A%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%2C%20and%20those%20securing%20not%20less%20than%201%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20votes%20in%20the%20last%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20state%20legislative%20assembly%20elections%20are%20eligible%20to%20receive%20electoral%20bonds.%20Furthermore%2C%20these%20bonds%20can%20only%20be%20encashed%20by%20eligible%20political%20parties%20through%20an%20authorised%20bank%20account%2C%20as%20specified%20in%20the%20notification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202019%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20declined%20to%20stay%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20stating%20the%20need%20for%20a%20comprehensive%20hearing%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bweighty%20issues%26quot%3B%20raised%20by%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20The%20current%20Constitution%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20BR%20Gavai%2C%20JB%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20began%20hearing%20arguments%20on%20October%2031%20last%20year.%20The%20petitions%20included%20those%20filed%20by%20Congress%20leader%20Jaya%20Thakur%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20and%20the%20NGO%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR).%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707958980000%