20use.%20If%20your%20nail%20clippers%20get%20wet%2C%20dry%20them%20thoroughly%20before%20storing%20them%20indoors%20in%20a%20plastic%20or%20cloth%20bag%20with%20all%20of%20the%20grinding%20accessories.%20If%20nail%20clippers%20or%20grinders%20are%20left%20outside%20and%20exposed%20to%20dampness%20and%20temperature%20extremes%2C%20the%20metal%20can%20rust%2C%20and%20the%20plastic%20can%20warp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20often%20should%20I%20trim%20my%20dog's%20nails%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20depends%20on%20your%20dog%2C%20but%20the%20general%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20trim%20your%20dog's%20nails%20before%20they%20grow%20long%20enough%20to%20click%20on%20the%20floor.%20All%20nails%20grow%20at%20different%20rates%2C%20and%20dogs%20wear%20them%20down%20differently.%20Big%2C%20heavy%20dogs%20that%20run%20around%20outside%20may%20naturally%20wear%20their%20nails%20down%2C%20requiring%20less%20frequent%20trimming.%20%26quot%3BA%20Yorkie%20that%20barely%20touches%20the%20ground%20most%20days%20might%20need%20a%20nail%20trim%20every%20two%20weeks%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Smits.%20%26quot%3BAn%20Iditarod%20training%20or%20marathon%20running%20pal%20might%20never%20need%20one.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20far%20down%20do%20I%20cut%20the%20nail%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETrim%20the%20nail%20as%20short%20as%20you%20can%20without%20cutting%20into%20the%20quick%2C%20which%20is%20the%20vein%20that%20runs%20down%20the%20center%20of%20the%20nail.%20If%20your%20dog%20has%20white%20nails%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20the%20quick.%20If%20your%20dog%20has%20black%20nails%2C%20it's%20harder%20to%20know%20precisely%20how%20far%20to%20cut.%20Conservatively%20clip%20just%20the%20hooked%20part%20of%20the%20nail%20to%20be%20safe.%20You%20can%20also%20ask%20your%20veterinarian%20for%20a%20demonstration%20on%20your%20dog.%20For%20more%20detailed%20directions%2C%20check%20out%20our%20tutorial%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fhow-to-cut-dog-nails%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20cut%20or%20grind%20your%20dog's%20nails%20the%20right%20way%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhen%20should%20I%20start%20trimming%20my%20puppy's%20nails%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20nail%20trimming%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20so%20your%20puppy%20learns%20to%20accept%20it.%20Even%20older%20dogs%20can%20learn%20to%20accept%20nail%20trimming%20if%20you%20approach%20it%20the%20right%20way.%20%26quot%3BIntroduce%20the%20dog%20to%20the%20nail%20trimming%20procedure%20in%20a%20slow%2C%20fun%2C%20rewarding%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20Smits%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20will%20enable%20the%20dog%20to%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20the%20attention%20that%20comes%20with%20getting%20a%20pedicure%20and%20time%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDoes%20nail%20trimming%20hurt%20my%20dog%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20you%20don't%20cut%20too%20far%20down%2C%20it%20hurts%20no%20more%20than%20trimming%20your%20own%20nails.%20However%2C%20be%20very%20careful%20not%20to%20cut%20the%20quick.%20The%20quick%20is%20extremely%20sensitive.%20Cutting%20into%20it%20is%20painful%20and%20will%20cause%20the%20nail%20to%20bleed.%20It%20may%20also%20cause%20your%20dog%20to%20become%20resistant%20to%20nail%20trimming%20in%20the%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20should%20I%20do%20if%20I%20cut%20my%20dog's%20nail%20and%20it%20starts%20to%20bleed%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20accidentally%20nick%20the%20quick%2C%20use%20styptic%20power%20to%20cauterize%20it%20and%20stop%20the%20bleeding.%20Scoop%20up%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20powder%20onto%20your%20finger%20or%20with%20a%20piece%20of%20gauze%20and%20press%20it%20gently%20but%20firmly%20against%20the%20nail.%20Hold%20for%20a%20minute%20or%20so%20until%20the%20bleeding%20stops.%20If%20you%20don't%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_081728_best-dog-nail-clippers-20%26h%3D6714e03286e71f11a95bd777353dcd677a3414d0fb059d23dd0e10559bf53309%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f41d79%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fbest-dog-nail-clippers%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.chewy.com%252Fmiracle-care-kwik-stop-styptic-powder%252Fdp%252F111488%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estyptic%20powder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20can%20use%20flour%20or%20corn%20starch%20instead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EI'm%20too%20nervous%20to%20trim%20my%20dog's%20nails.%20Who%20will%20do%20it%20for%20me%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20uncomfortable%20trimming%20your%20dog's%20nails%20or%20are%20concerned%20your%20pet%20might%20bite%20if%20you%20try%20to%20trim%20their%20nails%2C%20seek%20professional%20help.%20Most%20groomers%20include%20nail%20trimming%20in%20their%20regular%20services.%20You%20can%20also%20make%20an%20appointment%20to%20have%20your%20dog's%20nails%20trimmed%20at%20your%20veterinary%20hospital.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20dog%20is%20an%20amiable%20sort%2C%20groomers%20are%20a%20phenomenal%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Smits.%20However%2C%20dogs%20who%20may%20become%20aggressive%20during%20nail%20trimming%20would%20benefit%20from%20a%20trim%20at%20the%20vet's%20office%20where%20they%20can%20use%20sedation%20if%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-nail-clippers%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707948280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cd36d594aa8ee8e84b80d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-nail-clippers%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best%20dog%20nail%20clippers%20and%20grinders%20can%20cut%20small%20and%20large%20dogs'%20nails.%20Here%20are%20the%20top-rated%20trimmers%20we%20tested%20on%20both%20thick%20and%20black%20nails.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jlfranza%40yahoo.com%20(Jackie%20Brown%2CKarie%20Johnson)%22