%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-launches-strikes-on-lebanon-after-rocket-attack-13071585%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Defeat%20of%20a%20BJP%20Minister%2C%20Appointed%20Without%20an%20Election%2C%20Revives%20Constituent%20Assembly%20Debates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08233747%2FSurendra-Pal-Singh-T.-T..jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJaipur%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20defeat%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-rajasthan-minister-surender-pal-singh-tt-loses-bypoll%5C%22%3ESurendra%20Pal%20Singh%20T.T.%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Karanpur%20seat%20of%20Rajasthan%20has%20invoked%20memories%20of%20crucial%20questions%20posed%20in%20the%20Indian%20Constituent%20Assembly%2076%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fsa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D%26ved%3D2ahUKEwiQoaf99aqEAxV8-DgGHe5mAvIQFnoECAwQAw%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%252Fcity%252Fjaipur%252Frajasthan-minister-in-bhajan-lal-sharma-govt-loses-election-in-sriganganagars-karanpur%252Farticleshow%252F106634614.cms%26usg%3DAOvVaw0pbgonEvJ6a8Aru6DZ6fYp%26opi%3D89978449%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20minister%20immediately%20after%20losing%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2030%2C%201948%2C%20within%20the%20halls%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%2C%20deliberations%20unfolded%20around%20Articles%2060%2C%2061%20and%2062%20of%20the%20draft%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20K.T.%20Shah%2C%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20from%20Bihar%20with%20roots%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20posed%20numerous%20questions%20that%20compelled%20Dr.%20Bhim%20Rao%20Ambedkar%20to%20exert%20considerable%20effort%20in%20countering%20his%20arguments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20query%20revolved%20around%20whether%20MLAs%20and%20MPs%20should%20seek%20a%20fresh%20election%20upon%20their%20induction%20into%20the%20cabinet.%20This%20would%20challenge%20the%20appointment%20process%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20or%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20revolved%20around%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20MP%20or%20MLA%20selected%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20or%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20as%20a%20suitable%20minister%20may%20not%20align%20with%20the%20criteria%20deemed%20eligible%20by%20the%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20contended%20that%20once%20appointed%20as%20a%20minister%2C%20an%20elected%20member%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20should%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20obtain%20a%20vote%20of%20confidence%20within%20the%20respective%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20implies%20that%20following%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20government%2C%20once%20the%20formalities%20of%20securing%20a%20vote%20of%20confidence%20in%20the%20House%20are%20fulfilled%2C%20each%20minister%20should%20also%20seek%20a%20vote%20of%20trust%20from%20that%20same%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20moved%20an%20amendment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0(2A)%20On%20every%20change%20in%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%2C%20and%20particularly%20on%20every%20change%20of%20the%20holder%20of%20Prime-Ministership%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20(alternatively%2C%20the%20President)%20shall%20present%20the%20new%20minister%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%20to%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20House%20of%20Parliament%2C%20and%20shall%20ask%20for%20a%20vote%20of%20confidence%20from%20that%20body%20in%20the%20particular%20minister%20newly%20appointed.%20In%20the%20event%20of%20an%20adverse%20vote%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20particular%20minister%2C%20the%20minister%20concerned%20shall%20forthwith%20cease%20to%20hold%20office%20and%20a%20new%20minister%20appointed.%20If%20a%20vote%20of%20confidence%20in%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%20collectively%20is%20refused%2C%20the%20Council%20as%20a%20whole%20shall%20resign%20and%20a%20new%20Ministry%20formed%20in%20its%20place%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20December%2030%2C%201948.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%2C%20Debates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20debate%2C%20which%20lasted%20extensively%2C%20was%20held%20by%20H.V.%20Kamat%2C%20Tajammul%20Hussain%2C%20Mahavir%20Tyagi%2C%20Rajbahadur%2C%20Qazi%20Syed%20Karimuddin.%20Various%20scholars%2C%20including%20Santhanam%2C%20Lakshminarayan%20Sahu%2C%20and%20Mohammad%20Tahir%2C%20also%20participated%20in%20the%20debate%2C%20stressing%20on%20improving%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20and%20implementing%20new%20ethical%20standards%20regarding%20the%20appointments%20of%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20questions%2C%20Ambedkar%20explained%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20true%20that%20in%20the%20early%20history%20of%20the%20British%20Cabinet%2C%20every%20person%20who%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament%2C%20if%20he%20was%20appointed%20a%20minister%2C%20was%20required%20to%20resign%20his%20seat%20in%20Parliament%20and%20to%20seek%20re-election%20because%20it%20was%20felt%20that%20a%20person%2C%20if%20he%20is%20appointed%20a%20Minister%2C%20will%20likely%20to%20be%20under%20the%20influence%20of%20the%20Crown%20and%20do%20things%20in%20a%20manner%20not%20justified%20by%20public%20interest.%20The%20British%20themselves%20have%20now%20given%20up%20that%20system%3B%20by%20a%20statute%20they%20abrogated%20that%20rule%20and%20no%20person%20or%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20who%20is%20appointed%20a%20Minister%20is%20now%20required%20to%20seek%20re-election.%20That%20provision%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20quite%20unnecessary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20December%2030%2C%201948.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%2C%20Debates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20termed%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20amendments%20as%20completely%20%E2%80%9Cunnecessary%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20that%20they%20are%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20impractical%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Ambedkar%20definitely%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20I%20explained%20a%20little%20while%20ago%2C%20if%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20does%20happen%20to%20appoint%20a%20minister%20who%20is%20not%20worthy%20of%20the%20post%2C%20it%20would%20be%20perfectly%20possible%20for%20the%20Legislature%20to%20table%20a%20motion%20of%20no-confidence%20either%20in%20that%20particular%20minister%20or%20in%20the%20whole%20ministry%20and%20thereby%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20or%20of%20the%20minister%20or%20of%20the%20minister%20if%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20not%20prepared%20to%20dismiss%20him%20on%20the%20call%20of%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20December%2030%2C%201948.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%2C%20Debates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20lot%20of%20concerns%20were%20raised%20about%20the%20distrust%20of%20the%20voters%20towards%20the%20ministers%2C%20Ambedkar%20finally%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EIs%20it%20not%20desirable%2C%20is%20it%20not%20sufficient%20that%20we%20should%20trust%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20the%20legislature%20and%20the%20public%20at%20large%20watching%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20ministers%20and%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20legislature%20to%20see%20that%20no%20such%20infamous%20thing%20is%20done%20by%20either%20of%20them%3F%20I%20think%20this%20is%20a%20case%20which%20may%20eminently%20be%20left%20to%20the%20good%20sense%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20to%20the%20good%20sense%20of%20the%20legislature%20with%20the%20general%20public%20holding%20a%20watching%20brief%20upon%20them.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20December%2030%2C%201948.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%2C%20Debates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20Ambedkar%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20therefore%2C%20say%20that%20these%20amendments%20are%20unnecessary%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20appeared%20as%20though%20he%20had%20never%20anticipated%20an%20episode%20akin%20to%20that%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpictures-phone-location-other-evidence-show-brij-bhushan-allegedly-making-advances%5C%22%3EMP%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%3C%2Fa%3E%20unfolding.%20The%20position%20from%20which%20he%20had%20sought%20to%20safeguard%20the%20dignity%20of%20MPs%20and%20ministers%20seemed%20to%20have%20turned%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20such%20occurrences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fambedkar-constitution-assembly-democracy%5C%22%3ELessons%20for%20Today%20in%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20Last%20Address%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20public%20has%20asserted%20its%20decisive%20power%2C%20emphasising%20that%20the%20authority%20lies%20with%20the%20people%20rather%20than%20in%20the%20presumptuous%20decision%20to%20appoint%20individuals%20like%20Surendra%20Pal%20Singh%20T.T.%20as%20ministers%20even%20before%20their%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20would%20be%20really%20interesting%20to%20think%20that%20a%20new%20mandate%20can%20be%20taken%20from%20the%20public%20through%20the%20re-election%20of%20the%20ministers%20made%20in%20the%20government%20(be%20it%20the%20central%20government%20or%20the%20state%20governments)%2C%20as%20constitutional%20scholars%20like%20Shah%20had%20advised%20that%20despite%20being%20made%20a%20minister%2C%20ultimately%20the%20public%20should%20decide%20whether%20he%20is%20really%20worthy%20of%20being%20made%20a%20minister%20or%20else%20the%20public%20may%20give%20even%20more%20shocking%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20was%20professor%20K.T.%20Shah%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20was%20not%20only%20an%20expert%20in%20economics%2C%20he%20was%20also%20a%20renowned%20jurist.%20He%20was%20a%20student%20of%20London%20School%20of%20Economics.%20He%20was%20considered%20so%20talented%20that%20he%20received%20membership%20of%20Gray%E2%80%99s%20Inn.%20It%20was%20Shah%20who%20challenged%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20in%20the%20election%20for%20the%20post%20of%20President.%20He%20was%20originally%20a%20Gujarati%20and%20was%20a%20good%20playwright%20in%20the%20Gujarati%20language.%20He%20was%20elected%20member%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constituent%20Assembly%20from%20Bihar.%20His%20contribution%20in%20the%20making%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20huge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20had%20debated%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20itself%20to%20keep%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98secular%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20constitution.%20He%20struggled%20a%20lot%20for%20the%20important%20role%20of%20the%20judiciary%20in%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20Shah%20had%20twice%20submitted%20amendments%20to%20add%20the%20words%20secular%2C%20federal%20and%20socialist%20in%20Article%201%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20the%20case%20of%20Sri%20Karanpur%20and%20Surendra%20Pal%20Singh%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20extraordinary%20political%20incident%20took%20place%20during%20the%20process%20of%20elections%20to%20the%20Rajasthan%20assembly.%20Voting%20was%20postponed%20when%20Congress%20candidate%20Gurmeet%20Singh%20Kunnar%2C%20from%20the%20Karanpur%20assembly%20constituency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fjaipur%2Fcong-candidate-from-karanpur-seat-dies-election-adjourned%2Farticleshow%2F105247971.cms%5C%22%3Epassed%20away.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20that%20were%20held%20for%20199%20seats%20out%20of%20200%2C%20the%20BJP%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Frajasthan-assembly%2Frajasthan-election-results-december-3-2023-bjp-congress-live-updates%2Farticle67597833.ece%5C%22%3Esecured%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20majority%20by%20winning%20115%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Karanpur%20seat%2C%20Congress%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestatesman.com%2Findia%2Fcongress-fields-rupinder-singh-kunnar-for-karanpur-assembly-polls-1503250020.html%5C%22%3Edeclared%3C%2Fa%3E%20Gurmeet%20Singh%20Kunnar%E2%80%99s%20son%20Rupinder%20Singh%20Kunnar%20as%20its%20fresh%20candidate.%20However%2C%20chief%20minister%20Bhajanlal%20Sharma%20appointed%20Surendra%20Pal%20Singh%20as%20a%20minister%20even%20before%20the%20bypolls%20were%20held%2C%20aiming%20to%20ensure%20his%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20voting%20day%20came%20closer%20in%20Sri%20Karanpur%20and%20the%20first%20cabinet%20expansion%20of%20the%20Bhajan%20Lal%20government%20in%20Rajasthan%20started%2C%20people%20were%20shocked%20when%20Surendra%20Pal%20Singh%20was%20being%20sworn%20in%20to%20be%20included%20in%20the%20state%20cabinet%20even%20before%20being%20elected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20very%20surprising%20because%20perhaps%20it%20has%20never%20happened%20in%20the%20electoral%20history%20of%20India%20that%20a%20candidate%20has%20been%20made%20a%20minister%20even%20before%20the%20voting.%20But%2C%20despite%20making%20him%20a%20minister%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20area%20defeated%20him%20and%20the%20historic%20manoeuvre%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20did%20not%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETribhuvan%20is%20a%20senior%20political%20journalist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707921030000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08233747%2FSurendra-Pal-Singh-T.-T..jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-defeat-of-surender-pal-bjp-minister-without-winning-a-poll-revives-constituent-assembly-debates%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Surendra%20Pal%20Singh%20T