igcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20RVDC%20method%20established%20by%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20and%20his%20team%20at%20IIT-Guwahati%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECan%20Municipal%20Corporations%20use%20this%20new%20technique%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20institute%2C%20Professor%20Ajay%20Kalamdhad%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20proven%20technique%20not%20only%20handles%20sizable%20quantities%20of%20organic%20waste%20but%20also%20offers%20immediate%20application%20feasibility%20for%20municipal%20corporations%2C%20industries%2C%20sewage%20treatment%20facilities%2C%20aquatic%20weeds%20and%20various%20organic%20waste%20management%20sectors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20scaled-up%20process%20successfully%20produced%20100%20to%20150%20kg%20of%20vermicompost%20within%20a%20month%20from%20250%20to%20300%20kg%20of%20daily%20waste%20fed.%20The%20increased%20earthworm%20count%20resulted%20in%20the%20secondary%20end%20product%20being%20the%20earthworm%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20study%20included%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332396%2Fhow-to-make-bio-enzymes-from-kitchen-waste-at-home-diy-steps-by-kolkata-gardener-nita-singh%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evegetable%20waste%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20aquatic%20weed%20(water%20hyacinth)%20as%20prime%20substrates%2C%20both%20in%20mono-substrate%20composting%20and%20co-composting.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20entire%20study%2C%20we%20have%20converted%2015%20tonnes%20of%20waste%20collected%20from%20the%20markets%20and%20ponds%20around%20the%20IIT%20Guwahati%20campus%20(350%20kg%20per%20day).%20The%20confidence%20that%20we%20gained%20through%20the%20study%20is%